1
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:35,597
We did not think that karting
could become a career.

2
00:01:35,679 --> 00:01:36,681
AYRTON'S FATHER
MILTON DA SILVA

3
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:40,270
But it has become a
big part of our lives

4
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:46,471
and we are a bit worried because
then along came Formula One.

5
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,038
May God protect him forever.

6
00:01:49,238 --> 00:01:50,239
AYRTON'S MOTHER
NEYDE SENNA

7
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:52,959
All the dangers are my biggest fear.

8
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:56,032
I would like to thank him
because he is a good son

9
00:01:56,120 --> 00:02:00,955
and this year he has worked
very hard and honestly.

10
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:04,194
For me, it is more important than any title.

11
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,152
The time has come.

12
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:42,074
Ayrton is ready to ride in a Formula
One car for the first time.

13
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:47,758
I believe it was God
who gave me this opportunity,

14
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,838
I've been waiting for a long time.

15
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:54,590
And now it is helpful
to remain calm, tranquil, relaxed.

16
00:03:30,661 --> 00:03:33,754
1984

17
00:03:34,661 --> 00:03:36,754
Ayrton, this is a beautiful city,

18
00:03:36,830 --> 00:03:40,527
with wonderful streets to walk,
but unsuitable to host a race, no?

19
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,624
REGINALDO LEME

20
00:03:42,302 --> 00:03:44,532
Indeed. I arrived at the last minute

21
00:03:44,771 --> 00:03:47,205
and I was surprised.
I've never been to Monaco.

22
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:50,533
I did some testing

23
00:03:50,610 --> 00:03:54,569
And fortunately, I managed
to adapt to the track.

24
00:03:54,981 --> 00:03:59,441
There is no margin for error:
any error would result in an accident.

25
00:03:59,753 --> 00:04:01,414
But for now, I'm satisfied.

26
00:04:04,491 --> 00:04:07,756
I was travelling a lot, as a
Formula One journalist

27
00:04:07,827 --> 00:04:10,762
when Ayrton began to be noticed
driving a Toleman.

28
00:04:10,830 --> 00:04:11,819
VOICE OF REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

29
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:17,063
Toleman was not a winning team.

30
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:23,138
The car was bad and never won a race.

31
00:04:23,476 --> 00:04:28,812
That's why what Ayrton did in Monaco
was true genius.

32
00:05:08,521 --> 00:05:13,618
Ayrton Senna overtakes Keke Rosberg
gaining third position.

33
00:05:17,697 --> 00:05:18,721
VOICE OF GALVÃO BUENO
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

34
00:05:18,798 --> 00:05:22,029
And overtakes Niki Lauda!

35
00:05:22,135 --> 00:05:26,196
Ayrton Senna
takes second place!

36
00:05:26,439 --> 00:05:29,602
At the most dangerous part of the track!

37
00:05:36,449 --> 00:05:37,939
VOICE OF JAMES HUNT
1976 FORMULA ONE WORLD CHAMPION

38
00:06:13,987 --> 00:06:15,818
Incredible!

39
00:06:20,593 --> 00:06:23,756
Ayrton raises his arms
and gestures with enthusiasm!

40
00:06:24,064 --> 00:06:27,158
Celebrating as if he won the race!

41
00:06:27,467 --> 00:06:29,492
If we had continued for a few more laps,

42
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:33,801
I am sure Ayrton would have passed him.

43
00:06:35,975 --> 00:06:37,943
I had a serious chance of winning.

44
00:06:38,211 --> 00:06:41,305
But until you cross the finishing line
in first position,

45
00:06:41,448 --> 00:06:42,642
it is impossible to make a prediction.

46
00:06:42,816 --> 00:06:46,308
Formula One is politics, money

47
00:06:46,753 --> 00:06:50,450
and while you are making your way through it,
you must deal with such things.

48
00:07:05,638 --> 00:07:08,664
Ayrton Senna
the new star of Formula One!

49
00:07:09,709 --> 00:07:12,200
Appearing for the first time
on the Formula One podium

50
00:07:12,479 --> 00:07:14,743
after a fantastic performance.

51
00:07:22,589 --> 00:07:23,578
JOHN BISIGNANO

52
00:07:54,893 --> 00:07:57,353
1985

53
00:07:59,893 --> 00:08:04,353
LOTUS

54
00:08:08,268 --> 00:08:09,257
VOICE OF JOHN BISIGNAGNO
ESPN COMMENTATOR

55
00:09:10,964 --> 00:09:13,091
Even as a child, he
always knew what he wanted

56
00:09:14,434 --> 00:09:17,096
and he always got it.

57
00:09:17,503 --> 00:09:18,765
AYRTON'S MOTHER
NEYDA SENNA

58
00:09:18,838 --> 00:09:22,103
For example, he always paid attention
in the classroom at school,

59
00:09:22,275 --> 00:09:24,743
so he didn't have to study at home

60
00:09:24,811 --> 00:09:28,577
and so he had more time
to play on his go-kart.

61
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:39,090
VOICE OF RICHARD WILLIAMS
SPORTS JOURNALIST, THE GUARDIAN

62
00:10:11,824 --> 00:10:16,056
PORTUGUESE GRAND PRIX - APRIL 21st 1985
AYRTON'S SECOND RACE WITH LOTUS

63
00:10:21,834 --> 00:10:23,859
Ayrton was exceptional when it rained.

64
00:10:23,937 --> 00:10:25,063
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

65
00:10:25,338 --> 00:10:30,332
When the conditions were bad
and the track became slippery

66
00:10:30,410 --> 00:10:31,775
he had a higher gear.

67
00:10:44,524 --> 00:10:46,754
The Estoril race was incredible.

68
00:10:47,593 --> 00:10:50,994
He lapped all his opponents except one.

69
00:10:55,101 --> 00:10:58,332
It is wonderful!
An extraordinary feeling.

70
00:10:59,339 --> 00:11:03,241
I am very happy because,
in my second year in Formula One,

71
00:11:03,576 --> 00:11:07,034
I managed to fulfill my first dream,
which was to win my first Grand Prix.

72
00:11:13,286 --> 00:11:15,117
It is something unique.

89
00:11:32,538 --> 00:11:34,938
MILI OKADA
FUJI TV

90
00:11:45,351 --> 00:11:49,785
I think many Japanese girls are fans of Mr. Senna.

91
00:11:49,789 --> 00:11:52,417
Now I am close to him
and I'm so nervous...

92
00:13:43,407 --> 00:13:46,431
ALAIN PROST
WORLD CHAMPION 1985, 1986

93
00:13:47,407 --> 00:13:49,431
SELINA SCOTT
WOGAN TALK SHOW, BBC

94
00:15:12,325 --> 00:15:18,025
The first year at McLaren
was decisive in the life of Ayrton.

95
00:15:18,097 --> 00:15:19,086
VIVIANE SENNA
AYRTON'S SISTER

96
00:15:20,499 --> 00:15:22,228
He was very nervous.

97
00:15:22,768 --> 00:15:26,226
It was as if he bore the weight
of the world on his shoulders

98
00:15:26,806 --> 00:15:31,505
because he now had the responsibility

99
00:15:31,577 --> 00:15:35,980
to demonstrate he was a 
first rate driver.

100
00:16:52,792 --> 00:16:57,957
MONACO GRAND PRIX
14 May 1988

101
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:27,733
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
30th OCTOBER 1988

102
00:20:35,381 --> 00:20:37,941
It is the fifteenth Grand Prix of the season.

103
00:20:38,517 --> 00:20:41,111
As the sun rises, Brazil will await the chequered flag

104
00:20:41,186 --> 00:20:45,953
and for Ayrton Senna to win
his first world title in Formula One,

105
00:20:46,425 --> 00:20:50,259
realising a dream he had
since he was a child.

106
00:20:54,402 --> 00:20:58,426
VOICE OF PIERRE VAN VILET
TF1 COMMENTATOR

107
00:21:08,948 --> 00:21:11,473
We are about to start.
Green light.

108
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:12,808
Senna does not start!

109
00:21:16,355 --> 00:21:20,257
Prost came out ahead
while Ayrton Senna was left behind.

110
00:21:22,194 --> 00:21:25,254
Ayrton Senna is in 14th place.

111
00:21:26,832 --> 00:21:29,060
I thought, "So long title. It's over".

112
00:21:29,167 --> 00:21:32,225
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

113
00:21:34,406 --> 00:21:38,399
He takes eighth place.
An amazing comeback from Senna.

114
00:21:47,987 --> 00:21:50,421
Then his favourite thing happened,

115
00:21:50,489 --> 00:21:51,888
it began to rain.

116
00:21:53,726 --> 00:21:55,887
Senna is now in fourth position.

117
00:21:56,795 --> 00:21:59,628
Senna runs, runs, runs!

118
00:22:05,333 --> 00:22:07,302
Ayrton Senna overtakes Prost and onwards!

119
00:22:17,549 --> 00:22:20,575
I started giving thanks
during the last lap.

120
00:22:20,753 --> 00:22:22,414
I thanked God.

121
00:22:22,554 --> 00:22:26,456
It was incredible. I could not believe
I was going to win the championship,

122
00:22:27,626 --> 00:22:30,993
Despite all the anxiety and tension.

123
00:22:31,897 --> 00:22:33,762
I felt God's presence.

124
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,059
I have seen God

125
00:22:37,903 --> 00:22:41,339
It was a very special moment for me.

126
00:22:42,174 --> 00:22:44,608
An indescribable feeling.

127
00:22:44,843 --> 00:22:47,368
It remains engraved in my
memory and as a part of me.

128
00:22:56,689 --> 00:22:59,817
Ayrton Senna of Brazil!

129
00:23:00,159 --> 00:23:04,687
World Champion 1988!

130
00:23:06,665 --> 00:23:09,156
SAO PAULO

131
00:23:19,545 --> 00:23:21,740
What an incredible race!

132
00:23:22,181 --> 00:23:28,381
A great victory.
He had to come from 16th place.

133
00:23:30,789 --> 00:23:36,159
AYRTON SENNA
WORLD CHAMPION 1988

134
00:23:40,966 --> 00:23:44,595
Ayrton, how do you feel
as World Champion?

135
00:23:44,903 --> 00:23:47,235
I feel so much peace.

136
00:23:47,573 --> 00:23:50,133
It is as if someone had removed
a huge weight

137
00:23:50,442 --> 00:23:52,603
from my shoulders and head.

138
00:23:52,811 --> 00:23:57,874
It is difficult to understand what it means
to be a World Champion.

139
00:23:58,550 --> 00:24:02,384
SAO PAULO
15th NOVEMBER 1988

140
00:24:15,801 --> 00:24:17,735
He is an amazing person, wonderful.

141
00:24:17,803 --> 00:24:22,540
He is very humble and imporoves the
image of Brazil abroad.

142
00:24:22,841 --> 00:24:24,968
He shares his victory with us.

143
00:24:25,144 --> 00:24:26,270
I admire him very much.

144
00:24:26,445 --> 00:24:27,503
He is a very brave man.

145
00:24:27,579 --> 00:24:28,637
I just know this.

146
00:24:28,714 --> 00:24:29,840
We are proud of him.

147
00:24:30,582 --> 00:24:33,415
It is one of the few things
that we can still be proud of.

148
00:24:33,719 --> 00:24:37,246
Once, I asked Ayrton
"When will you think about quitting?"

149
00:24:37,322 --> 00:24:40,553
He said, "Mum, the day I am
the champion I will stop."

150
00:24:40,759 --> 00:24:43,990
In my heart,
I knew that was not true.

151
00:24:44,163 --> 00:24:45,323
We all know that.

152
00:24:46,131 --> 00:24:51,967
SENNA FAMILY HOME VIDEO

153
00:24:52,604 --> 00:24:55,004
SENNA'S FAMILY AND THE
FAMILY OF TAMIN ANGRA

154
00:24:56,275 --> 00:24:57,333
VIVIANE SENNA
AYRTON'S SISTER

155
00:24:57,409 --> 00:25:00,401
After the 1988 Championship,
after he won the title,

156
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:07,216
We noticed that he had changed between
the beginning and the end of the year.

157
00:25:08,554 --> 00:25:12,752
Because he had found himself.

158
00:25:12,825 --> 00:25:15,055
He had discovered who he was.

159
00:25:15,127 --> 00:25:20,121
It was a process that reached
its conclusion after his championship victory.

160
00:25:29,374 --> 00:25:31,001
At Christmas, many things happen.

161
00:25:31,076 --> 00:25:32,441
New friends are made,

162
00:25:33,111 --> 00:25:35,011
like the person I'm about to introduce.

163
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:36,104
XUXA MENEGHEL
BRAZILIAN TV STAR

164
00:25:36,782 --> 00:25:38,477
He was part of my 1988.

165
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:40,450
Ayrton Senna.

166
00:25:49,094 --> 00:25:51,153
Isn't he cute?

167
00:25:52,397 --> 00:25:55,332
I have a few questions for you.

168
00:25:56,301 --> 00:26:00,567
I think everybody is excited,
but none more than me,

169
00:26:00,639 --> 00:26:05,973
It is not easy to talk.
Ayrton is now my friend.

170
00:26:06,044 --> 00:26:09,138
Ayrton, what do you want for Christmas?

171
00:26:09,214 --> 00:26:11,375
As a Christmas present?

172
00:26:11,950 --> 00:26:15,386
What I really want, I cannot say here!

173
00:26:15,454 --> 00:26:17,012
Why not?

174
00:26:17,456 --> 00:26:22,291
It would be censored.
Let's say I just want to be happy.

175
00:26:22,361 --> 00:26:24,352
Whisper it to me.

176
00:26:31,169 --> 00:26:32,830
Happy New Year.

177
00:26:33,605 --> 00:26:35,038
Happy 1990.

178
00:26:35,741 --> 00:26:37,641
Happy '91.

179
00:26:37,709 --> 00:26:39,233
Happy '92.

180
00:26:39,511 --> 00:26:41,570
Happy '93.

181
00:27:05,103 --> 00:27:08,195
VOICE OF RON DENNIS
MCLAREN TEAM MANAGER

182
00:27:51,717 --> 00:27:53,082
Senna and Prost. Prost and Senna.

183
00:27:53,185 --> 00:27:55,119
The order of the grid is always one or the other.

184
00:27:55,587 --> 00:27:56,918
It is a war between them.

185
00:27:57,055 --> 00:27:58,647
For the French driver Alain Prost,

186
00:27:58,724 --> 00:28:01,852
he believes his teammate is unfair to him.

187
00:28:01,927 --> 00:28:04,862
and these disagreements could
affect the rest of the season.

189
00:28:09,134 --> 00:28:12,763
Grand Prix after Grand Prix they were
more and more distant from each other.

190
00:28:12,838 --> 00:28:13,964
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

191
00:28:14,072 --> 00:28:15,835
Ayrton said:
"This Frenchman is tough.

192
00:28:16,241 --> 00:28:17,333
"He wants war."

193
00:28:19,211 --> 00:28:20,508
After a little more time,

194
00:28:20,912 --> 00:28:23,540
they became completely isolated
and they didn't speak anymore.

195
00:28:26,918 --> 00:28:31,048
JEAN-MARIE BALESTRE
FIA PRESIDENT

196
00:28:58,116 --> 00:29:02,610
I would like to give a warm welcome to
the President of FISA, Mr. Balestre.

197
00:29:05,992 --> 00:29:08,050
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
PRE-RACE DRIVERS MEETING

198
00:29:42,262 --> 00:29:45,490
VOICE OF JOHN BISIGNANO
ESPN COMMENTATOR

199
00:30:02,214 --> 00:30:07,310
JAPANESE GRAND PRIX
22nd OCTOBER 1989

200
00:30:18,797 --> 00:30:20,788
Prost is first. Senna, second.

201
00:30:21,066 --> 00:30:23,034
Prost jumped into the lead.

202
00:30:23,101 --> 00:30:24,568
His start was better.

203
00:30:42,521 --> 00:30:45,684
LAP 45 OF 53, CASIO CHICANE

204
00:30:56,101 --> 00:30:59,127
LAP 46 OF 53, CASIO CHICANE

205
00:31:07,712 --> 00:31:10,340
Finally they clash! It goes in the favour of Prost.

206
00:31:10,916 --> 00:31:16,513
If the race ends like this,
Prost wins the title.

207
00:31:17,155 --> 00:31:22,559
But, for Ayrton Senna it is a no win situation.

208
00:31:56,094 --> 00:31:57,425
Nannini passes.

209
00:31:57,796 --> 00:32:00,356
Nannini is now in the lead.

210
00:32:04,135 --> 00:32:05,898
Senna is still in the pits.

211
00:32:10,575 --> 00:32:14,306
Senna is back on track,
but he is far behind Nannini.

212
00:32:14,379 --> 00:32:16,040
Catching up is almost impossible.

213
00:32:16,281 --> 00:32:19,307
It's all or nothing,
five laps to go.

214
00:32:19,384 --> 00:32:22,842
It will be a suicidal race for Senna,
if he decides to try anything.

215
00:32:24,055 --> 00:32:25,955
Then Prost saw Ayrton return to the race

216
00:32:26,057 --> 00:32:27,081
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

217
00:32:27,158 --> 00:32:30,127
and immediately went to the stewards' office.

218
00:32:35,166 --> 00:32:37,157
Nannini, first. Senna, second.

219
00:32:37,502 --> 00:32:39,834
Senna tries to pass Nannini!

220
00:32:39,904 --> 00:32:42,338
Senna is in the lead!

221
00:32:42,407 --> 00:32:43,431
LAP 51 OF 53, CASIO CHICANE.

222
00:32:44,442 --> 00:32:45,966
Waving Brazilian flags!

223
00:32:46,144 --> 00:32:48,169
All stand up!

224
00:32:48,346 --> 00:32:49,438
Ayrton Senna.

225
00:32:49,614 --> 00:32:51,946
The checkered flag!

226
00:32:52,117 --> 00:32:53,812
Senna celebrates in the cockpit.

227
00:32:53,918 --> 00:32:56,942
AYRTON SENNA WINNER - JAPANESE GRAND PRIX

228
00:32:57,020 --> 00:33:00,588
He hits his helmet.
The Brazilian Ayrton Senna.

229
00:33:01,092 --> 00:33:04,528
Visibly moved,

230
00:33:05,263 --> 00:33:08,926
He raises his visor
and wipes away a tear.

231
00:33:09,167 --> 00:33:11,863
It is a fantastic victory.

232
00:33:12,137 --> 00:33:14,401
I have never seen anything like it.

233
00:33:22,947 --> 00:33:25,279
There was no podium celebration
immediately after the race.

234
00:33:26,150 --> 00:33:27,408
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

235
00:33:32,991 --> 00:33:36,392
STEWARDS OFFICE

236
00:33:39,698 --> 00:33:45,261
As the wait was prolonged, the more people feared
that the decision was becoming political.

237
00:34:04,356 --> 00:34:07,082
The decision taken by the
team of FIA Commissioners

238
00:34:07,192 --> 00:34:09,319
at the Grand Prix of Japan

239
00:34:10,462 --> 00:34:13,454
is to exclude the number one car
and its driver, Ayrton Senna,

240
00:34:13,698 --> 00:34:15,563
from the final outcome of the race.

241
00:34:15,667 --> 00:34:20,698
After the race, a giant screen has
repeatedly shown the incident

242
00:34:21,906 --> 00:34:24,568
and everything that happened to
enable Senna's return to the track.

243
00:34:24,876 --> 00:34:28,869
After reviewing these images,
race officials have concluded

244
00:34:28,947 --> 00:34:33,415
that Senna failed to use the
chicane to resume racing

245
00:34:33,485 --> 00:34:37,251
Senna has infringed Article 56
of the FIA regulations.

246
00:35:34,380 --> 00:35:37,404
REPLAY AUSTRIAN GRAND PRIX 1981

247
00:36:35,807 --> 00:36:39,831
FIA HEADQUARTERS - PARIS
The Court of Appeals declares

248
00:36:40,144 --> 00:36:44,308
a six-month license suspension for Senna.

249
00:36:46,284 --> 00:36:50,181
A warning not only to Ayrton
Senna but for all the drivers,

250
00:36:51,055 --> 00:36:54,149
And a fine of $100,000.

251
00:36:54,225 --> 00:36:58,059
While he is one of the best drivers in the world,

252
00:36:58,396 --> 00:37:02,730
you have no right to
cause stupid accidents.

253
00:37:29,561 --> 00:37:32,223
That was quite a profound moment for Ayrton

254
00:37:32,297 --> 00:37:33,321
VIVIANE SENNA

255
00:37:33,398 --> 00:37:36,629
because Balestre had behaved
even worse than Prost.

256
00:37:38,136 --> 00:37:41,071
He even thought about giving
up Formula One racing.

257
00:37:47,579 --> 00:37:48,603
VOICE OF RON DENNIS
MCLAREN TEAM MANAGER

258
00:38:37,362 --> 00:38:40,229
All drivers aspire towards their limits.

259
00:38:40,598 --> 00:38:45,467
My limit is different from that of Prost.
This is the reality.

260
00:38:45,803 --> 00:38:51,105
Instead of trying
to improve his own capacity,

261
00:38:51,442 --> 00:38:54,411
he found it easier to attack me.

262
00:39:04,956 --> 00:39:08,824
The fact that I believe in God,
the fact that I have faith in God,

263
00:39:09,661 --> 00:39:11,754
is not to say that I am immortal,

264
00:39:11,829 --> 00:39:19,602
It does not mean that I am immune from
danger, as has been said.

265
00:39:20,038 --> 00:39:23,701
I'm afraid of hurting myself
just like everyone else,

266
00:39:23,941 --> 00:39:27,711
especially driving in Formula One,
where the threat is constant.

