00:48:29,788 --> 00:48:31,812
FIA AWARDS
PARIS 1990

280
00:49:03,322 --> 00:49:05,746
JACKIE STEWART
FORMULA ONE WORLD CHAMPION 1969, 1971, 1973

281
00:50:23,300 --> 00:50:25,632
Two of the greatest champions
in the history of Formula One

282
00:50:26,036 --> 00:50:27,560
ended up in the sand.
Championship ruined.

283
00:50:27,638 --> 00:50:30,869
They accuse each other,
but Prost was the hardest.

284
00:50:30,941 --> 00:50:32,465
His reaction was violent.

285
00:50:32,543 --> 00:50:39,107
I wanted to punch him in the
face, but I was so disgusted

286
00:50:39,183 --> 00:50:41,344
that I did not succeed.

287
00:50:41,418 --> 00:50:42,885
It makes me feel sick.

288
00:52:06,370 --> 00:52:11,137
The situation in Brazil
was very negative and depressing.

289
00:52:11,208 --> 00:52:12,539
VIVIANE SENNA
AYRTON'S SISTER

290
00:52:12,643 --> 00:52:16,773
But many times,
when Ayrton won,

291
00:52:17,014 --> 00:52:21,348
instead of trying to hide
his Brazilian origins, as others did,

292
00:52:21,585 --> 00:52:24,816
he did the opposite,
waving the flag of his country.

293
00:52:25,222 --> 00:52:27,747
He took it inside the car every Sunday.

294
00:52:27,991 --> 00:52:32,826
He was an inspiration to people.
That's why they loved him so much.

296
00:52:44,341 --> 00:52:47,208
Ayrton had never won the
Grand Prix of Brazil.

297
00:52:47,277 --> 00:52:48,335
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

298
00:52:48,545 --> 00:52:54,881
Since he entered Formula One he always
dreamed of winning in his home country.

299
00:52:57,020 --> 00:52:59,250
BRAZILIAN GRAND PRIX
21st MARCH 1991

300
00:52:59,323 --> 00:53:01,655
The Brazilian Grand Prix has begun.

301
00:53:01,725 --> 00:53:03,454
Red light. Green light.

302
00:53:03,527 --> 00:53:05,154
A good start.

303
00:53:05,496 --> 00:53:06,690
Come on, Senna!

304
00:53:06,864 --> 00:53:09,128
Senna is in command.

305
00:53:18,742 --> 00:53:20,004
LAP 54/67

306
00:53:24,517 --> 00:53:26,609
VOICE OF RON DENNIS
MCLAREN TEAM MANAGER

307
00:53:33,457 --> 00:53:35,516
Here's Senna. It's starting to rain.

309
00:53:35,592 --> 00:53:36,684
It's raining. It must stop.

310
00:53:48,138 --> 00:53:49,628
7 LAPS REMAINING

311
00:53:50,107 --> 00:53:54,410
It seems impossible to drive a
Formula One car stuck in sixth gear.

312
00:53:54,478 --> 00:53:55,467
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

313
00:53:55,546 --> 00:53:59,642
Ayrton wanted to stop.
He could no longer drive it.

314
00:54:00,350 --> 00:54:04,514
But he had already tried many times
to win the Brazilian Grand Prix

315
00:54:04,655 --> 00:54:07,852
and found a special force within himself.

316
00:54:17,734 --> 00:54:20,726
The last corner.
And Senna crosses the line.

317
00:54:20,804 --> 00:54:22,066
Go for the win!

318
00:54:22,139 --> 00:54:27,771
Ayrton, Ayrton ...
The Brazilian Ayrton Senna!

319
00:54:30,747 --> 00:54:35,684
In the lead from start to
finish, he wins at lnterlagos!

320
00:54:37,154 --> 00:54:40,351
A wonderful victory for Senna!

321
00:54:48,131 --> 00:54:49,621
No way!

322
00:54:55,405 --> 00:55:00,869
God damn it, I won!

323
00:55:21,398 --> 00:55:25,858
 ( Prost ) "son of a bitch"

324
00:55:28,972 --> 00:55:31,202
He won and then fainted.

325
00:55:31,274 --> 00:55:32,366
REGINALDO LEME
GLOBO TV COMMENTATOR

326
00:55:33,176 --> 00:55:35,474
It was his most heroic moment.

327
00:55:55,265 --> 00:55:57,233
Because of the tremendous physical effort,

328
00:55:57,300 --> 00:56:00,792
I had muscle spasms of my
shoulder and neck.

329
00:56:01,872 --> 00:56:03,737
The pain was tremendous.

330
00:56:04,841 --> 00:56:07,969
The physical and mental stress
this weekend was unheard of.

331
00:56:09,346 --> 00:56:11,075
But there could be only one result.

332
00:56:11,148 --> 00:56:14,174
I finished the race with no more energy.

333
00:56:29,800 --> 00:56:31,734
Come here, Dad. Come on.

334
00:56:32,636 --> 00:56:33,728
Come here.

335
00:56:42,646 --> 00:56:44,238
Quiet, Ayrton.

336
00:56:52,189 --> 00:56:53,816
Today, I fought hard.

337
00:56:53,990 --> 00:56:58,586
I wanted to finish the race
and finish in first position,

338
00:56:58,662 --> 00:57:01,028
because He is the greatest

339
00:57:01,298 --> 00:57:03,630
and He will give me this
race after all.

340
00:57:03,700 --> 00:57:06,328
That's what happened.

341
00:57:06,436 --> 00:57:08,802
It is God who gave me this race
and I'm happy.

342
00:57:08,872 --> 00:57:10,840
It was thrilling.

343
00:58:00,857 --> 00:58:04,850
All hail the Brazilian Senna
for his victory. Congratulations.

345
00:58:04,995 --> 00:58:07,463
I thank all of Brazil.
I thank all the fans.

346
00:58:07,531 --> 00:58:11,126
This weekend I felt so
much warmth around me

347
00:58:11,201 --> 00:58:14,193
that we could not do anything but win.

348
00:58:14,271 --> 00:58:16,102
It could not have been any other way.

349
00:58:16,273 --> 00:58:17,331
And we did.

350
00:58:24,681 --> 00:58:28,640
SENNA FAMILY HOUSE, SAO PAULO

351
00:59:22,706 --> 00:59:29,270
Ayrton was so well known in Brazil

352
00:59:29,346 --> 00:59:30,472
VIVIANE SENNA
AYRTON'S SISTER

353
00:59:30,547 --> 00:59:33,038
there were a lot of people asking for help

354
00:59:34,251 --> 00:59:38,187
for personal problems. Sometimes hospitals

355
00:59:38,255 --> 00:59:42,157
and charities sought his
support and donations.

326
00:59:43,793 --> 00:59:47,354
Ayrton gave donations and tried to work things out.

357
00:59:48,265 --> 00:59:51,291
But did not want to make random donations.

358
00:59:51,368 --> 00:59:59,339
He wanted to develop a whole thing,
something organized and structured

359
00:59:59,776 --> 01:00:04,270
to help Brazil, especially the children.

330
01:00:17,396 --> 01:00:20,454
VOICE OF JOHN BISIGNANO
ESPN COMMENTATOR

